[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To solicit in love; to court.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Each, like the Grecian artist, <qex>wooes</qex>⟦br⟧
The image he himself has wrought.</q> <rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To court solicitously; to invite with
importunity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thee, chantress, oft the woods among⟦br⟧
I <qex>woo</qex>, to hear thy even song.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I <qex>woo</qex> the wind⟦br⟧
That still delays his coming.</q> <rj><qau>Bryant.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Woo</ent>⟦br⟧

